cs.CV, cs.HC, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.IT

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper primarily focuses on integrating computer vision techniques with eye-tracking technology to support radiologists' reading experience with an automatic image segmentation task. 
2. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) - The study involves the use of eye-tracking technology to create a visual attention map, which can be considered as a human-computer interaction task. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with medical image segmentation, which can be considered as a multimedia task. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper involves the use of computer-derived saliency information to find foreground and background cues for the object of interest, which can be considered as an artificial intelligence task. 
5. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper involves the use of information theory concepts such as dice similarity coefficient and Hausdorff distance to evaluate the segmentation accuracy of the proposed system.
